diff:1616289852:1616289852:=1,69d0%0a%3c (:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!LanguageOfTheNacirema]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Philosophy Lessons from HAND%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: Russell_E%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c The HAND is a very important symbol in Nacirema culture. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c The HAND is a very important symbol in Nacirema culture. You can lend someone a HAND to help them. You can also praise someone by giving them a HAND, or by HANDing it to them. A worker is a HAND, and an excellent worker might be your right HAND man. Tools can be HANDy. You might need to hold someone’s HAND through a rough experience. You ask someone’s HAND in marriage, and you try your HAND at a novel activity. You can be dealt a good HAND in cards or in life. If you acquire something, you get your HANDs on it. Heavy-HANDed describes something overbearing or overdone. Any sort of greeting can be called a HANDshake. If you’re able to HANDle something, you understand it. HAND has many meanings. On the other HAND, some of these uses must just be coincidences.%0a%3c %0a%3c The Nacirema obsession with hands shows that Nacirema culture is fundamentally manipulative. Whether helping someone, observing someone, or working on one’s own, the Nacirema always focus on control. They want to be as directly involved as possible, preferably physically pushing or pulling things the way they want. The use of hands in Nacirema speech is clearly indicative of a need to command whatever is being discussed.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: E:)%0a%3c (:Category: LanguageOfTheNacirema:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
